l#UnitChoices\">UnitChoices</a>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#UnitDependent.scaleUnit\">UnitDependent.scaleUnit</a> <span class=\"fn\">u1</span> <span class=\"fn\">u2</span> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#isDimensionallyCorrect_iff","kind":"theorem","line":461,"name":"isDimensionallyCorrect_iff","sourceLink":"https://github.com/HEPLean/PhysLean#L461-L463"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#IsDimensionallyCorrect\"><span class=\"name\">IsDimensionallyCorrect</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./PhysLean/Units/UnitDependent.html#UnitDependent\">UnitDependent</a> <span class=\"fn\">M</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <span class=\"fn\">M</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Prop</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A term of type `M` carrying an instance of `UnitDependent M` is said to be\ndimensionally correct if under a change of units it remains the same.\n\nMore colloquially, something is dimensionally correct if it (e.g. it's value or its truth\nfor a proposition) does not depend on the units it is written in.\n\nFor the case of `m : M` with `CarriesDimension M` then `IsDimensionallyCorrect m`\ncorresponds to the statement that `m` does not depend on units, e.g. is zero\nor the dimension of `M` is zero.\n","docLink":"./PhysLean/U